canonical:
  title: 祝上羅漢齋疏
  author: 崔惟淸
  language: lzh
  text: 伏以赴感應機覺皇之妙德歸美報上臣子之至忠弟子賦材甚踈輔國無狀重罹譴責幾淪深穽之中忽被甄收如蹈靑霄之上光生二州之地恩洗八載之勞雖衰疲無理穎之能而懇倒有祝高之願躬趨寶刹恭辦珍羞普延四果之眞僧寔薦萬年之遐筭伏願聖上陛下福祥雲集戩穀川增劫石易消保慶基之益固海田屢變仰聖曆之長新
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 祝上羅漢齋疏
  author: 崔惟淸
  language: lzh
  text: 伏以赴感應機。覺皇之妙德。歸美報上。臣子之至忠。弟子賦材甚踈。輔國無狀。重罹譴責。幾淪深穽之中。忽被甄收。如蹈靑霄之上。光生二州之地。恩洗八載之勞。雖衰疲無理穎之能。而懇倒有祝高之願。躬趨寶刹。恭辦珍羞。普延四果之眞僧。寔薦萬年之遐筭。伏願聖上陛下。福祥雲集。戩穀川增。劫石易消。保慶基之益固。海田屢變。仰聖曆之長新。
korean:
  title: 축 상라한재 소
  author: 최유청
  language: kor
  text: 삼가 생각하건대, 감응을 좇아 기미(機微)에 보응하는 것은 부처님[覺星]의 신묘한 공덕이고, 아름다운 이름을 임금에 돌려 은혜에 보답하는 것은, 신자(臣子)의 지극한 충성인 것입니다. 제자(弟子 불교를 신봉하는 자)인 저는 타고난 자질이 매우 소루하여서, 나라에 보답하는 일에 잘못됨이 많아 깊이 견책을 입고, 거의 깊은 함정 속으로 빠지는 것 같더니, 홀연히 죄를 사면하시고 거두어 주심을 입게 되어, 하늘에라도 뛰어오를 것같이 기쁩니다. 빛은 두 주(州)의 땅에 빛나고, 은혜는 8년의 노고를 씻어 주었습니다. 비록 노쇠하고 피로하여서 뛰어난 능력은 없으나, 임금을 축복하려는 소원은 간절합니다. 몸소 불사(佛寺)에 나아가서 삼가 진귀한 제물을 바치고 널리 도가 높은 참된 스님을 맞아다가 이에 임금님의 만년 장수(萬年長壽)를 빕니다. 엎드려 원하옵건대, 성상폐하께서는 복과 상서가 구름같이 엉기고, 복록이 냇물 불어나듯 하여, 겁석(劫石)이 부서질 때까지 왕위를 더욱 공고히 보전하시고, 상전벽해가 여러 번 변할 때까지 임금님의 연세가 길이 새로움을 바라옵나이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1130_030_0040&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: A Prayer Offering at the Arhat Feast Ritual
  author: Choe Yuyeong
  language: eng
  text: |-
    I humbly reflect: that the Buddha responds to all sentient beings through subtle workings—such is the wondrous virtue of the Awakened One. That we return all beauty and merit to the throne in gratitude—such is the utmost loyalty of subjects and ministers.

    I am but a humble disciple, crude in talent and meager in gifts. Having failed in service to the realm, I fell deep into reproach, nearly swallowed by the abyss. Yet suddenly, mercy descended—my transgressions forgiven, my person restored. Joy seized me as though I had leapt into the blue heavens themselves.

    Light now shines upon two provinces; grace has washed away eight years of toil. Though weakened by age and want of exceptional skill, my heart burns with fervent prayer for the sovereign's blessing.

    I proceed with reverent steps to the sacred temple, where I humbly lay before it precious offerings. I invite the great monks of enlightenment to gather, that through their virtues I may call down ten thousand years of longevity upon His Majesty.

    I prostrate myself with this ardent wish: May blessings descend like gathering clouds upon the throne; may fortune flow like waters running full. When even the mountains of kalpas crumble to dust, may the realm's foundation only grow more secure. Through countless ages of heaven and earth transformed, may the sovereign's years stretch ever long and ever new.
  footnotes:
    - The 'two provinces' likely refer to regions under royal patronage or the author's jurisdiction.
    - Eight years of toil may reference a specific period of hardship or service preceding the author's rehabilitation.
    - The 'Arhat Feast' (羅漢齋) was a Buddhist ritual in which monks were invited to receive alms and merit was generated through their participation.
    - This piece is a ritual prayer-document (疏), which employs formal court language and Buddhist terminology to petition for the sovereign's longevity and the realm's prosperity.
